    "department": "Office of the CEO",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nInterested in influencing the course of an iconic, fast-growing technology business? Curious to learn from, and accelerate growth alongside, some of the most accomplished leaders in tech today? Read on!\n\n\nTHE ROLE OVERVIEW\n\nAt Snowflake, we are at the core of the AI revolution - both in serving our customers with the AI data cloud, and internally, in how we operate day to day. We are seeking a high-leverage, AI-fluent strategic thinker to serve as a key partner to our CEO and Executive Team. This is a rare \"seat at the table\" for an early-career professional who possesses the rare blend of traditional strategic rigor and modern AI-native workflows. You will not just manage the rhythm of the business nor advise at a distance on strategy; you will architect the future of Snowflake from the CEO’s office, using agentic AI and advanced data reasoning to implement innovative solutions across all Snowflake functions.\n\nWork Location: This position is based exclusively in Menlo Park, CA. Alternative locations are not available at this time.\n\n\nOUR IDEAL STRATEGIC LEADER WILL HAVE:\n\nMinimal Qualifications\n\n - 2-3 Years of \"Hyper-Growth\" Experience: A background in top-tier strategy, consulting, or high-growth technology environments with demonstrated impact on business outcomes\n\n - AI-Native DNA: You don't just \"use\" AI; it is fundamental to how you work. You are proficient in Prompt Engineering, agentic workflows, and basic Python/SQL to manipulate data directly within the Snowflake AI Data Cloud.\n\n - High-Velocity Problem Solving: The ability to navigate complex business landscapes with a \"systems thinking\" mindset. You see the connections between product, sales, and finance that others miss.\n\n - Executive Presence with Low Ego: You are comfortable presenting to the C-Suite and Board, yet you possess the discretion and humility required to thrive in a \"behind-the-scenes\" high-impact role.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n - Computer Science bachelor’s degree or equivalent hands-on experience\n\n - Communication Mastery: Exceptional ability to translate \"technical speak\" into \"business impact.\" You can draft a CEO-level memo that is both visionary and grounded in data.\n\n\nWHY THIS IS AN INCREDIBLE OPPORTUNITY\n\nThis role is a career catapult. You will gain a decade’s worth of executive experience in two years. You will be at the epicenter of the AI revolution, helping to steer a company that provides the data \"fuel\" for the rest of the world’s AI initiatives.\n\nThe \"Snowflake Standard\": We value people who are driven, disciplined, and relentless about delivering value. If you are an AI-native thinker who wants to help run the engine of a global tech giant, we want to talk to you.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
